  "description": [
    "business here he coaxed as Benton started for the dor The advertising man paused A curious look came into his eyes he saw the vision of a mangled little hand Ill take you up he said slowly You may tell your readers that Ive come here to make Greenhorn fammic iirwlor hie hronth hp nrlHed or in famous yWO days later after sending and receiving several innocentappearing telegrams Benton went to Gordon a town a hundred miles north of Greenfield where he met Joseph Kerns head of the Kerns Detective Agency and Jim Hayes a former newspaper photographer who had graduated into the movies He told them what he wanted and whyand they promised to do their part If he gets away with it said Kerns to Hayes on their way back to New York Greenfield will be no place for a person with a weak heart And it Royce is subject to apoplexy supplemented Hayes hed better take out more insurance The day after he returned from Gordon Benton ran his tirst advertisement in the Greenfield papers In the center of the back page surrounded with a goodly border of white space the people of the town read THROUGH"
